                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Miracles of Mary (Tä'ammərä
                            Maryam), Miracles of Jesus (Tä'ammərä Iyassus)<p>Illustration: Fol. 2v: Drawing of Virgin Mary and the Christ
                                Child with angels with drawn swords and broad decorative border.
                                </p><p> Illustration: Fol. 110v: Miniature of Joachim and Hannah
                                with large orange border and with notes above their heads: "How
                                Joachim prayed" and "How Saint Hannah prayed". </p><p> Fol. 1v: Note
                                of the sale of the manuscript in faint ballpoint pen in another
                                hand. States the date is Tər 26, 1928 EC. Sellers, the buyer, and
                                the witnesses names included. </p><p> Fols. 3r, 13r, 15r, passim:
                                Original owner noted at the beginning of each miracle, in the
                                intercession: "Virgin Mary be with Wäldä Maryam." </p><p> Owner:
                                Wäldä Maryam.</p><p> No scribe listed.</p><p> Gift of Bruce Willsie,
                                Princeton Class of 1986.</p><p>One column, probably as a pen
                                trial.</p><p>The Story of the Infant Mary in the Temple (not in
                                Budge or Herolt).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary accepted the Book of her
                                Miracles compiled by Saint Hildefonsus [Däqsəyos], Bishop of Toledo
                                (Budge, Mary 1; Strelcyn 15, 1.1; Bland 1; Romances, Cleopatra
                                7).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary spoke from her picture to a devout
                                worshipper (Budge, Mary 2; Strelcyn 15, 1.3).</p><p>How the midwife
                                Salome glorified Jesus (not in Budge; Strelcyn 16, 3).</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary appeared to the dying scribe Damianus (Budge, Mary,
                                4).</p><p>How Abbas, Bishop of Rome, cut off his hand which had been
                                kissed by a woman when he was celebrating the Eucharist, and how the
                                Virgin Mary rejoined it to his arm (Budge, Mary, 5).</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary appeared to Isaac, the monk, and promised to take him to
                                herself after three days (Budge, Mary, 6).</p><p>How Jesus entered
                                the temple [Presentation of Jesus in the Temple] (Strelcyn 16,
                                5).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary appeared out of her picture to Mary,
                                the daughter of a certain God-fearing man, and promised to take her
                                to Paradise after three days (Budge, Mary, 7).</p><p>How a painter
                                was saved by the Virgin Mary when he fell from a scaffold (Budge,
                                Mary, 8).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary carried a sick person from the
                                Monastery of the Pilgrims to Jerusalem and showed him where Jesus
                                was crucified and buried and baptized him in the waters of the
                                Jordan (Budge, Mary, 9).</p><p>How Jesus recovered the stolen cattle
                                of a man called Tətəməna in Nazareth (Strelcyn 16, 8).</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary appeared to a Roman youth called Zacharias who crowned
                                her icon with roses and how she saved him from bandits because they
                                saw roses flowing from his mouth when he recited her sälam and how
                                they converted and became monks (Budge, Mary, 10)</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary recovered the stolen property of two women called
                                Juliana and Barbara, when they were on pilgrimage to Jerusalem
                                (Budge, Mary, 11).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary saved two Muslims from
                                the storm when they called on her name (Budge, Mary, 12).</p><p>How
                                Jesus recovered the stolen calf in Palestine after commanding it to
                                speak.</p><p>How the Virgin Mary moved the Monastery of Ekona
                                (Budge, Mary, 13).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary healed the eyes of
                                Yohannəs Bäkänəsi, the blind priest in Egypt, by anointing him with
                                milk from her breasts (Budge, Mary, 14).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary
                                healed the merchant from Colossae after being shot in the eye with
                                an arrow by pirates (Budge, Mary, 15).</p><p>How the lion glorified
                                Jesus before Joseph the Carpenter (Strelcyn 16, 11).</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary restored the sight of Elizabeth, a blind girl, with her
                                breath and milk (Budge, Mary, 16).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary
                                arranged marriages for two poor girls called Martha and Yäwahit
                                (Budge, Mary, 17).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary delivered the soul of
                                the scribe who was writing the book of her miracles (Budge, Mary,
                                18).</p><p>How Jesus saved the adulterer from stoning (Strelcyn 16,
                                14?).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary delivered from prison a certain man
                                called Giyorgis (Budge, Mary, 19).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary
                                protected the elderly priest called Qätir (Budge, Mary,
                                20).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary sent Saint George to threaten a Qädi
                                (Islamic leader) for imprisoning a Christian (Budge, Mary,
                                21).</p><p>How Jesus healed the blind (Strelcyn 16, ?).</p><p>How
                                the Virgin Mary healed a man with a stone foot (Budge, Mary,
                                22).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary healed a person called Märqorəwos of
                                his leprosy (Budge, Mary, 23).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary appeared to
                                a person in the church Haratälom.</p><p>How Jesus raised from the
                                dead the son of the widow of Nain (Strelcyn 16.18,
                                32.16.30).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary aided in the delivery of a
                                child to an abbess before the bishop came to enquire into the matter
                                (Budge, Mary, 25; Bland 24 [but much shorter] also in Vincent de
                                Beauvais (from 1264)).</p><p>THow the Virgin Mary received the soul
                                of Barok, a dissolute man (Budge, Mary, 26).</p><p>How the Virgin
                                Mary received the soul of Anəsətasəyos (Budge, Mary, 27).</p><p>How
                                Jesus was baptized by John the Baptist (Strelcyn 16).</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary helped a monk to escape the monastery of Qäləmon when
                                persecuted by other monks (Budge, Mary, 28).</p><p>How the Virgin
                                Mary saved the soul of the cannibal of Qəmər (Budge, Mary,
                                29).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary delivered a thief, the son of a poor
                                widow (Budge, Mary, 30).</p><p>How the Jewish leader begged Pilate
                                to burn the body of Jesus (Strelcyn 16).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary
                                saved the woman in childbirth from drowning (Budge, Mary, 32;
                                Strelcyn 32.16.31; Bland 2; Romances, Cleopatra 3).</p><p>How the
                                Virgin Mary gave water to a thirsty dog (Budge, Mary, 33; Strelcyn
                                32.16. 32).</p><p>How the Virgin Mary gave a garment to a monk
                                (Budge, Mary, 93).</p><p>How Jesus rose from the dead (Strelcyn 16,
                                37).</p><p>How the Archangel Gabriel took the body of the Virgin
                                Mary.</p><p>the Virgin Mary appeared in the monastery of Däbərä
                                Mətəmaq.</p><p>How Jesus asked the Virgin Mary about her five
                                lamentations.</p><p>How the Virgin Mary appeared to the Syrian
                                potter and how he glorified her (Budge, Mary, 35).</p><p>How Jesus
                                recovered the fish stolen from a fisherman (Strelcyn 16,
                                9).</p><p>The Story of the Infant Mary in the Temple (not in Budge
                                or Herolt).</p><!--BIBLIOGRAPHY--><p>References: See references
                                listed in manuscript no. 8 and 41.</p></summary>
